                                                                    JUnit Class

Unit testing:-  Unit testing is a level of software testing where individual units/code of a software are tested.

Junit is an Unit testing framework.
 Junit 3 --> Strictly typed
 Junit 4 --> Advanced, less strictly typed.

 JUnit --> XUnit
                ---NUnit  --> asp
                ---PyUnit --> python
                ---JUnit  --> Java
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JUnit 3
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 YOu have to extend TestCase class for every test class you write
 ClassName has to be meaningful
 TestClass should contains Test along with className

 Every method should contain test before methodName

 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 JUnit 4
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 No need of writing extending a TestCase class
 No need of writing  test before every method

Annotations: Form of Metadata
                  data about data

Assertions : affirming statement
                       expected value, output

Thank You :)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@Ignore - which will skip the execution of particular test methods.

@Before - The method which contain this annotation will executed before the execution of any valid test method in your class.

@After  - The method which contain this annotation will executed after the execution of any valid test method in your class.


JUnit3
setup()
teardown()
specific methods available in JUnit 3 to implement the @Before and @After functionality.

@BeforeClass - The method which contain this annotation will be the very first thing in the class

@AfterClass -  The method which contain this annotation will be the very last thing in the class

@Test(timeout=50) - timeout feature


    assertEquals
		assertNotEquals
		assertNotNull
		assertNull
		assertTrue
		assertFalse
		assertSame
		assertNotSame
		assertArrayEquals

Thank you :)
